>> Subject: Questions
>>
>> Don,
>> Please confirm a few items.
>>
>> - Bolt provides P2PE and gateway services - correct?

>> Correct, the Bolt platform provides both P2PE and Gateway Services to facilitate the processing of
>> CNP (Card Not Present) transactions/data.
>>
>> - How many key sets are in use?

>>The Bolt platform currently houses/utilizes nine (9) distinct Key Sets — eight (8) of which are
>>currently active and in-use, and one (1) key set is decommissioned due to it being tied to a legacy
>>platform that has since been decommissioned.
>>
>> - What HSMs (vendor, model number) are the keys stored within?
>>
>> The majority of keys utilized within the environment, past and present, have been stored inside of
>> Thales/Gemalto PayShield 9000s.
>>
>> - How have the keys been managed in accordance with PCI P2PE standards?
>>
>> I tried to summarize as concisely as possible as it’s a very detailed answer.
>>
>> Key Blocks were created per PCI requirements and stored inside of Hardware Security Modules
>> (HSMs).
>> Key Components were printed to secured, tamper-evident forms by authorized personnel.
>> Key Components were hand-delivered from the secure room holding the HSMs to key custodians
>> located inside of locked combination safes, and the forms were witnessed and signed by key
>> custodians who accepted responsibility for management of the keys assigned.
